A video posted to Lowveld Media’s YouTube account shows a cash-in-transit heist reportedly taking place on the N4 near Crocodile Gorge on Wednesday afternoon. A report on the incident stated that around 10 suspects, using four vehicles, opened fire on a Fidelity Security armoured bakkie before stopping it and rigging it with explosives. The video was captured by a witness who was on the road when the explosion took place – as shown below. 